
                                            As today marks world Pneumonia Day, parents and caregivers are encouraged to be mindful of their habits around young children. 
                                         CAPE TOWN - As today marks World Pneumonia Day, parents and caregivers are encouraged to be mindful of their habits around young children. Pneumonia is an acute respiratory infection and the number one child-killer worldwide with one in five children dying as a result of pneumonia-related illnesses. The City of Cape Town says parents should be aware of the signs and symptoms of the disease Mayco member for safety and security JP Smith said, “As a society, we underestimate the harm done by smoking near babies and children, we have to be mindful of smoking near children.”